    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 14, 2026\n\n---\n\n## ⛴️ Iran Blockade Day 2: Trump Says He Doesn't Care. Oil Disagrees.\n\nThe US naval blockade of Iranian ports entered its second day. Trump, asked about new peace talks, said \"I don't care\" — then mentioned Iran had called and \"wants to work a deal.\" Thousands rallied in Tehran against the blockade.\n\n- **The economic read:** The IEA, World Bank, and IMF all warned in unison that fuel and fertilizer prices will stay elevated even if Hormuz reopens — shipping won't normalize quickly. Oil stays above $100/barrel.\n- **The diplomatic read:** France and the UK oppose the blockade. Pakistan is offering to host new talks. The US President has said he doesn't care. Diplomacy is proceeding normally.\n\n*The US declared a naval blockade of a sovereign nation and the President said he doesn't care whether it leads anywhere. Fine. Probably fine.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/liveblog/2026/4/14/iran-war-live-trump-claims-tehran-wants-a-deal-amid-us-blockade-of-hormuz) | [NBC News](https://www.nbcnews.com/world/iran/live-blog/live-updates-us-blockade-iran-ports-trump-hormuz-peace-talks-ceasefire-rcna331473)\n\n---\n\n## 🔨 Trump Threatened 50% Tariffs on Iran's Weapons Suppliers. The Supreme Court Already Ruled on This.\n\nTrump threatened 50% tariffs on any country supplying weapons to Iran — using the same legal mechanism the Supreme Court invalidated in February when it struck down his use of the IEEPA.\n\n- **The legal situation:** Analysts immediately called it an \"empty threat.\" The Supreme Court already removed this authority. Trump is threatening to use a tool the courts confiscated months ago.\n- **The intended target:** China and Russia, both reportedly moving weapons toward Iran. It's unclear how a legally unenforceable tariff changes that calculus.\n\n*Threatening sanctions with a legal authority the Supreme Court has already invalidated. Bold strategy.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/13/trump-threatens-50percent-tariffs-on-china-as-report-suggests-plans-for-arms-shipment-to-iran.html) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2026/4/8/trump-threatens-50-tariffs-on-countries-that-supply-iran-with-weapons)\n\n---\n\n## 💾 The US May Require Approval to Ship AI Chips Anywhere Outside America\n\nUS regulators are reportedly drafting rules that would require government approval to export AI chips to any country — not just China, not just adversaries. Everywhere.\n\n- **What's already moving:** The House Foreign Affairs Committee advanced a bill treating AI chip exports like weapons sales. Current rules already require case-by-case review for NVIDIA H200-equivalent chips heading to China.\n- **The trajectory:** A chip export control regime that started as a China containment strategy is quietly expanding into something much broader. NVIDIA, AMD, and their entire global customer base are in the middle.\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/05/us-reportedly-considering-sweeping-new-chip-export-controls/) | [ML Strategies](https://www.mlstrategies.com/insights-center/viewpoints/54031/2026-02-04-_026-ai-policy-and-semiconductor-outlook-how-federal)\n\n---\n\n## 🌍 The Iran War Is Redrawing the Middle East Map\n\nEgypt is reportedly reconsidering its decades-long policy of strategic balancing — potentially aligning toward a new \"Sunni Axis\" with Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Turkey, and Pakistan, according to geopolitical risk analysis.\n\n- **The trigger:** The US-Iran conflict has disrupted every regional country's default calculations. Egypt, which has long played both sides, is now under pressure to pick one.\n- **The bigger picture:** A bloc of Egypt, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, Turkey, and Pakistan would be a significant new regional force — assembled in direct response to a conflict the US started and Europe refused to support.\n\n*One naval blockade. Several regional alliance shifts. Zero quick solutions. Cool cool cool.*\n\n**Sources:** [Millennium Project](https://www.millennium-project.org/ecgi-april-2026-iran-war-shock-reshapes-regional-r/) | [Mr. Geopolitics](https://www.mrgeopolitics.com/p/the-week-ahead-in-geopolitics-april-13-2026)"
  }
]
